-- Raytheon posts lower quarterly profit
-- 
-- Thu Jan 27, 2011 7:08am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/01/27/us-raytheon-idUSTRE70Q33920110127

 

 ATLANTA  (Reuters) - Raytheon Co ( RTN.N ) posted lower quarterly earnings and forecast higher sales and per-share profit for this year. 

 The missile maker on Thursday said net income came to $459 million, or $1.25 a share, for the fourth quarter, compared with $504 million, or $1.30 a share, a year earlier. Sales rose 3 percent to $6.89 billion. (Reporting by  Karen Jacobs ; editing by John Wallace)